  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Before you start cooking, take your<strong> steaks </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let them adjust to room temperature</p><p>Chop the <strong>potatoes </strong>(skins on) into wedges</p><p>Add the <strong>potato wedges</strong> to one side of a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1685116632158-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1685116632158-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1685116632158-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1685116632158-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1685116632158-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>sweetcorn cobettes</strong> to a large piece of <strong>tin foil</strong> with a generous knob of <strong>butter</strong> and <strong>half</strong> the <strong>miso paste </strong>(save the rest for later!)</p><p>Scrunch the<strong> tin foil</strong> around the corn until tightly sealed and add to the other side of the baking tray – this is your <strong>miso butter corn</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until the corn is tender and the wedges are golden and crisp</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4? Use 2 trays!</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1685116635059-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1685116635059-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1685116635059-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1685116635059-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1685116635059-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Trim, then slice the <strong>spring onions</strong> finely</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1685116638852-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1685116638852-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1685116638852-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1685116638852-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1685116638852-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>soy sauce </strong>and<strong> mirin</strong> to a small bowl with the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, the <strong>remaining miso paste</strong>, <strong>ketchup</strong>, 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>Japanese-style BBQ sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1685116643239-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1685116643239-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1685116643239-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1685116643239-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1685116643239-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Pat the <strong>pork loin steaks</strong> dry with kitchen paper, then season both sides with <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>seasoned steaks</strong> and cook for 3 min on each side or until they're browned</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1685116647709-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1685116647709-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1685116647709-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1685116647709-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1685116647709-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once browned, add the <strong>Japanese-style BBQ sauce</strong> to the pan and cook for 2-3 min further or until the sauce has thickened and the pork is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>Once done, transfer the <strong>cooked steaks</strong> to a clean chopping board and leave them to rest for 2 min, reserving the sauce in the pan – this is your <strong>Japanese-style BBQ pork loin</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1685116651866-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
